/** 
 * Reset a node performing a soft or hard reset: <ul> <li>All other nodes are forgotten</li> <li>All the assigned / open slots are released</li> <li>If the node is a replica, it turns into a master</li> <li>Only for hard reset: a new Node ID is generated</li> <li>Only for hard reset: currentEpoch and configEpoch are set to 0</li> <li>The new configuration is saved and the cluster state updated</li> <li>If the node was a replica, the whole data set is flushed away</li> </ul>
 * @param hard {@code true} for hard reset. Generates a new nodeId and currentEpoch/configEpoch are set to 0
 * @return String simple-string-reply
 */
RedisFuture<String> clusterReset(boolean hard);
